      <!-- Section 7: Practical exercise -->
      <h2>Practical exercise</h2>

      <div class="quest-objective">
        <p>Create three copies of the same repo and verify they share the same history.</p>
        <ol>
          <li><span class="git-cmd">git clone</span> <code>mon-archive/</code> to <code>ma-copie/</code></li>
          <li>Create a <span class="keyword">bare repo</span> <code>archive-centrale.git</code></li>
          <li>Add it as a <span class="keyword">remote</span> in <code>mon-archive/</code> and push</li>
          <li><span class="git-cmd">git clone</span> from the <span class="keyword">bare repo</span> to <code>clone-depuis-bare/</code></li>
          <li>Verify that all 3 have the same history with <code>git log --oneline</code></li>
          <li>Run the verification script</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <h3>Prerequisites</h3>

      <p>You need the <code>mon-archive/</code> repo from quest 03. If you don't have it:</p>

      <pre data-lang="bash"><code>mkdir mon-archive && cd mon-archive
git init
echo "Bienvenue dans l'Archive" > README.md
git add README.md
git commit -m "Premier parchemin"
cd ..</code></pre>

      <h3>The commands</h3>

      <pre data-lang="bash"><code># 1. Clone local
git clone ./mon-archive ./ma-copie

# 2. Bare repo
git init --bare ./archive-centrale.git

# 3. Ajouter la remote et pousser
cd mon-archive
git remote add origine ../archive-centrale.git
git push origine main
cd ..

# 4. Clone depuis le bare repo
git clone ./archive-centrale.git ./clone-depuis-bare

# 5. Vérifier l'historique
cd mon-archive && git log --oneline && cd ..
cd ma-copie && git log --oneline && cd ..
cd clone-depuis-bare && git log --oneline && cd ..</code></pre>

      <h3>Verification</h3>

      <pre data-lang="bash"><code>bash verifier.sh</code></pre>

      <pre data-lang="powershell"><code>.\verifier.ps1</code></pre>

